The paper proposes a neural network architecture for executing natural language queries on a knowledge-base, which involves natural language processing (NLP), artificial intelligence (AI), and database (DB) technologies. The paper also mentions the use of gradient descent for training, which is a common optimization technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), falling under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed architecture through experiments, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG, and cs.IR, in that order.
